-- Kuwait's Americana chairman says not aware of potential sale
-- By Sylvia Westall and Ahmed Hagagy
-- Sun Apr 06, 2014 05:50AM EDT
-- None



KUWAIT, April 6 (Reuters) - Kuwait Food Co. (Americana) <FOOD.KW> is not aware of any potential sale of the company, its chairman said on Sunday.

Reuters reported on Thursday that Kuwait's billionaire al-Kharafi family was looking to sell Americana and had hired bankers to explore a deal. [ID:nL5N0MU4FI] "As executive, chairman and board we don't we know anything about anything on this subject," Americana Chairman Marzouk al-Kharafi told journalists on the sidelines of an annual general meeting in Kuwait.